<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem; font-style: italic;">Effective Date: January 2026</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">Welcome to ATLINE System. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard your information when you use our enterprise asset management and inventory tracking system. We are committed to protecting your privacy and ensuring the security of your personal information. Please read this privacy policy carefully. If you do not agree with the terms of this privacy policy, please do not access the system.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">1. INTRODUCTION AND SCOPE</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">This Privacy Policy applies to all information collected through our ATLINE System platform, including any related services, sales, marketing, or events. We reserve the right to make changes to this Privacy Policy at any time and for any reason. We will alert you about any changes by updating the "Last Updated" date of this Privacy Policy. You are encouraged to periodically review this Privacy Policy to stay informed of updates.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">The ATLINE System is designed to serve organizations in managing their internal and external assets, inventory tracking, employee management, helpdesk operations, credential management, and various other enterprise functions. As such, the system processes various types of data including personal information of employees, clients, vendors, and system users.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">This policy describes the types of information we may collect from you or that you may provide when you use the ATLINE System and our practices for collecting, using, maintaining, protecting, and disclosing that information. This policy applies to information we collect on this system, in email, text, and other electronic messages between you and this system, and through mobile and desktop applications you download from this system.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">2. INFORMATION WE COLLECT</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We collect information that you provide directly to us, information we obtain automatically when you use the system, and information from other sources. The categories of information we collect include:</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">2.1 Personal Information</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Personal information refers to any information that identifies or can be used to identify you directly or indirectly. This includes but is not limited to your full name, email address, telephone number, postal address, job title, department, employee identification number, and any other identifier by which you may be contacted online or offline. We collect this information when you register for an account, update your profile, or interact with various features of the system.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">2.2 Account Credentials</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">When you create an account, we collect your username, password, and security questions. Passwords are encrypted using industry-standard encryption algorithms and are never stored in plain text. We also collect two-factor authentication information if you enable this security feature, including authentication app tokens and recovery codes.</p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">2.3 Usage Data</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We automatically collect certain information when you access and use the system. This usage data includes your IP address, browser type and version, operating system, device information, pages visited, time and date of your visit, time spent on pages, unique device identifiers, and other diagnostic data. This information helps us understand how users interact with our system and allows us to improve functionality and user experience.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">2.4 Activity Logs</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">The system maintains comprehensive activity logs that record user actions within the platform. These logs include login and logout times, data modifications, file uploads and downloads, system configuration changes, and other significant activities. Activity logs are essential for security monitoring, compliance auditing, and troubleshooting purposes.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">2.5 Asset and Inventory Data</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">As an asset management system, we collect and store information about physical and digital assets including asset descriptions, serial numbers, purchase information, warranty details, location data, assignment history, maintenance records, and depreciation information. This data may be associated with individual users or departments.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">2.6 Communication Data</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We collect information contained in communications you send through the system, including helpdesk tickets, internal messages, comments, and any attachments. This includes the content of your communications, metadata such as timestamps and recipients, and any files or documents you share through the platform.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">3. HOW WE USE YOUR INFORMATION</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We use the information we collect for various purposes to provide, maintain, and improve our services. The specific uses include:</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">3.1 Service Provision and Maintenance</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We use your information to create and manage your account, authenticate your identity, provide access to system features based on your role and permissions, process transactions, and deliver the services you request. This includes managing asset assignments, processing helpdesk tickets, generating reports, and facilitating communication between users.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">3.2 System Improvement and Development</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We analyze usage patterns and user feedback to understand how our system is used and to identify areas for improvement. This analysis helps us develop new features, enhance existing functionality, optimize system performance, and create a better user experience. We may use aggregated and anonymized data for research and analytical purposes.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">3.3 Security and Fraud Prevention</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Your information is used to protect the security and integrity of our system. This includes detecting and preventing unauthorized access, identifying potential security threats, investigating suspicious activities, and enforcing our terms of service. We monitor system access patterns and maintain audit trails to ensure compliance with security policies.</p>

    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">3.4 Communication</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We use your contact information to send you important notifications about your account, system updates, security alerts, and changes to our policies. We may also send you operational communications related to your use of the system, such as password reset emails, two-factor authentication codes, and helpdesk ticket updates.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">3.5 Compliance and Legal Obligations</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We may use your information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, and legal processes. This includes responding to lawful requests from public authorities, enforcing our agreements, protecting our rights and property, and ensuring the safety of our users and the public.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">3.6 Business Operations</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We use information to support our business operations, including billing and invoicing, customer support, system administration, and internal reporting. This helps us manage our relationship with your organization and ensure the smooth operation of our services.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">4. DATA SHARING AND DISCLOSURE</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We do not sell, trade, or rent your personal information to third parties. However, we may share your information in the following circumstances:</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">4.1 Within Your Organization</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Information may be shared with other authorized users within your organization based on their roles and permissions. System administrators and managers may have access to user data, activity logs, and reports as necessary for their administrative functions. This sharing is governed by your organization's internal policies and access controls configured within the system.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">4.2 Service Providers</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We may share your information with third-party service providers who perform services on our behalf, such as cloud hosting providers, email delivery services, payment processors, and analytics providers. These service providers are contractually obligated to protect your information and may only use it for the specific purposes for which it was shared.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">4.3 Legal Requirements</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We may disclose your information if required to do so by law or in response to valid requests by public authorities, such as a court order, subpoena, or government investigation. We may also disclose information when we believe in good faith that disclosure is necessary to protect our rights, protect your safety or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or respond to a government request.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">4.4 Business Transfers</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">In the event of a merger, acquisition, reorganization, bankruptcy, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your information may be transferred as part of that transaction. We will notify you via email and/or a prominent notice on our system of any change in ownership or uses of your personal information.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">4.5 With Your Consent</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We may share your information with third parties when you have given us your explicit consent to do so. You will be informed of the specific purpose and recipient before any such sharing occurs, and you may withdraw your consent at any time.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">5. DATA SECURITY</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We implement comprehensive security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. Our security practices include:</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">5.1 Encryption</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">All data transmitted between your browser and our servers is encrypted using Transport Layer Security (TLS) protocol. Sensitive data stored in our databases, including passwords and credential information, is encrypted using industry-standard encryption algorithms. We regularly update our encryption methods to maintain the highest level of security.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">5.2 Access Controls</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We implement strict access controls to ensure that only authorized personnel can access your information. Our role-based access control system ensures that users can only access data and features appropriate to their role. Administrative access is limited to essential personnel and is subject to additional security measures.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">5.3 Authentication</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We support strong authentication mechanisms including complex password requirements and two-factor authentication. Users are encouraged to enable two-factor authentication for enhanced account security. We also implement session management controls to prevent unauthorized access to active sessions.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">5.4 Monitoring and Auditing</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Our systems are continuously monitored for security threats and suspicious activities. We maintain comprehensive audit logs of system access and data modifications. Regular security assessments and penetration testing are conducted to identify and address potential vulnerabilities.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">5.5 Data Backup and Recovery</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We perform regular backups of all system data to ensure business continuity and data recovery in case of system failures or disasters. Backup data is encrypted and stored securely in geographically distributed locations. We regularly test our backup and recovery procedures to ensure their effectiveness.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">5.6 Incident Response</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We have established incident response procedures to address security breaches promptly and effectively. In the event of a data breach that affects your personal information, we will notify you and relevant authorities as required by applicable law. Our incident response team is trained to contain, investigate, and remediate security incidents.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">6. DATA RETENTION</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected and to comply with our legal obligations. The retention period may vary depending on the type of information and the context in which it was collected:</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">6.1 Account Information</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Your account information is retained for as long as your account remains active. If your account is deactivated or deleted, we may retain certain information for a period of time to comply with legal obligations, resolve disputes, and enforce our agreements. After this retention period, your personal information will be securely deleted or anonymized.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">6.2 Activity Logs</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Activity logs and audit trails are retained for a minimum period as required by applicable regulations and your organization's compliance requirements. These logs are essential for security monitoring, compliance auditing, and forensic investigation purposes. The specific retention period may be configured by your system administrator.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">6.3 Asset and Transaction Data</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Asset records, inventory data, and transaction history are retained for the duration required by applicable accounting and tax regulations. This data may be retained for several years after the relevant assets are disposed of or transactions are completed to support audit and compliance requirements.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">6.4 Communication Records</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Helpdesk tickets, messages, and other communication records are retained according to your organization's document retention policies. These records may be archived after a certain period but remain accessible for reference and compliance purposes.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">7. YOUR RIGHTS AND CHOICES</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Depending on your location and applicable laws, you may have certain rights regarding your personal information:</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">7.1 Access and Portability</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">You have the right to request access to the personal information we hold about you. You may also request a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format. To exercise this right, please contact your system administrator or submit a request through the appropriate channels.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">7.2 Correction and Update</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">You have the right to request correction of any inaccurate or incomplete personal information we hold about you. You can update most of your account information directly through your profile settings. For other corrections, please contact your system administrator.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">7.3 Deletion</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">You may request deletion of your personal information, subject to certain exceptions. We may retain certain information as required by law or for legitimate business purposes. Deletion requests should be submitted to your system administrator, who will process them in accordance with applicable policies and regulations.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">7.4 Restriction and Objection</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">You may request that we restrict the processing of your personal information or object to certain processing activities. We will honor such requests where required by applicable law, unless we have compelling legitimate grounds to continue processing.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">8. COOKIES AND TRACKING TECHNOLOGIES</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to collect and store information about your interactions with our system:</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">8.1 Essential Cookies</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">These cookies are necessary for the system to function properly. They enable core functionality such as security, session management, and accessibility. You cannot opt out of essential cookies as they are required for the system to operate.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">8.2 Performance Cookies</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">These cookies collect information about how you use our system, such as which pages you visit most often and if you receive error messages. This information helps us improve system performance and user experience. Performance cookies do not collect information that identifies you personally.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">8.3 Functionality Cookies</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">These cookies allow the system to remember choices you make, such as your language preference, display settings, and other customizations. They provide enhanced, more personalized features and help us remember your preferences for future visits.</p>
    
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.5rem; font-weight: 500;">8.4 Managing Cookies</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Most web browsers allow you to control cookies through their settings. You can set your browser to refuse all cookies or to indicate when a cookie is being sent. However, if you disable cookies, some features of the system may not function properly.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">9. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">Your information may be transferred to and processed in countries other than your country of residence. These countries may have data protection laws that are different from the laws of your country. We take appropriate safeguards to ensure that your personal information remains protected in accordance with this Privacy Policy when transferred internationally.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">When we transfer personal information from the European Economic Area, United Kingdom, or Switzerland to other countries, we use appropriate legal mechanisms such as Standard Contractual Clauses approved by the European Commission, or we rely on other lawful bases for such transfers.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">10. CHILDREN'S PRIVACY</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">The ATLINE System is not intended for use by children under the age of 18. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 18. If you are a parent or guardian and believe that your child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately. If we discover that a child under 18 has provided us with personal information, we will take steps to delete such information from our systems.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">11. THIRD-PARTY LINKS AND SERVICES</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">The system may contain links to third-party websites, services, or applications that are not operated by us. This Privacy Policy does not apply to third-party services, and we are not responsible for the privacy practices of such third parties. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of any third-party services you access through our system.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We may integrate with third-party services to provide enhanced functionality, such as cloud storage providers, email services, and payment processors. When you use these integrated services, your information may be shared with the third-party provider in accordance with their privacy policies and our data sharing agreements.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">12. CHANGES TO THIS PRIVACY POLICY</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices, technologies, legal requirements, or other factors. When we make material changes to this Privacy Policy, we will notify you by updating the "Last Updated" date at the top of this policy and, where appropriate, provide additional notice such as adding a statement to the system homepage or sending you an email notification.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We encourage you to review this Privacy Policy periodically to stay informed about how we are protecting your information. Your continued use of the system after any changes to this Privacy Policy constitutes your acceptance of the updated policy.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">13. DATA PROTECTION OFFICER</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">If your organization is required to appoint a Data Protection Officer under applicable data protection laws, the DPO is responsible for overseeing compliance with this Privacy Policy and applicable data protection regulations. The DPO can be contacted through your organization's designated channels for any privacy-related inquiries or concerns.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">For organizations subject to the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) or similar regulations, the DPO serves as the primary point of contact for data subjects and supervisory authorities regarding data protection matters.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">14. REGULATORY COMPLIANCE</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We are committed to complying with applicable data protection laws and regulations, including but not limited to:</p>
    <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; list-style-type: disc; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
        <li>General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) for users in the European Economic Area</li>
        <li>Personal Data Protection Act (PDPA) for users in Malaysia and Singapore</li>
        <li>California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA) for California residents</li>
        <li>Other applicable national and regional data protection laws</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We implement appropriate technical and organizational measures to ensure compliance with these regulations and to protect your rights as a data subject.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1.5rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">15. CONTACT INFORMATION</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this Privacy Policy or our data practices, please contact:</p>
    <ul style="margin-left: 1.5rem; list-style-type: none; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">
        <li><strong>System Administrator:</strong> Contact your organization's IT department</li>
        <li><strong>Data Protection Inquiries:</strong> Submit through the system's helpdesk</li>
        <li><strong>Privacy Complaints:</strong> Contact your organization's compliance officer</li>
    </ul>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">We will respond to your inquiries within a reasonable timeframe and in accordance with applicable legal requirements. For data subject access requests and other formal privacy requests, we aim to respond within 30 days of receiving your request.</p>
</div>

<div style="margin-bottom: 1rem;">
    <h4 style="font-size: 13px; font-weight: 600; color: #111827; margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">16. ACKNOWLEDGMENT</h4>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">By using the ATLINE System, you acknowledge that you have read and understood this Privacy Policy and agree to the collection, use, and disclosure of your information as described herein. If you do not agree with this Privacy Policy, please do not use the system.</p>
    <p style="margin-bottom: 0.75rem;">This Privacy Policy is effective as of the date stated at the beginning of this document and will remain in effect except with respect to any changes in its provisions in the future, which will be in effect immediately after being posted on this page.</p>
</div>

